In order to achieve the minimum reflectance of the surface surrounded by a homogenous medium with a different refractive index, precise control of the thickness and refractive index of the coating material is essential. Generally, the refractive index and coating thickness must meet the following conditions to minimize the reflectance of the substrate to zero at a specific wavelength (λ)4,44,48:1nc=ns.naandtc=λ/(4×nc)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
